xtce:Parameter.name: SECHDR__TC
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: Count of microseconds (raw number is number of PCLK ticks) from the beginning of the most recent minute epoch

xtce:Parameter.name: MPUDATA__TRIGGER_ON_INT
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: 1 if measurement was triggered by an interrupt, 0 otherwise. If it was triggered by an interrupt, the timestamp is the captured timestamp of the interrupt and therefore the most accurate value.

xtce:Parameter.name: MPUDATA__TRIGGER_ON_TMOUT
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: 1 if measurement was triggered by timeout, 0 otherwise. If 1, the timestamp is the time that the I2C readout began, and therefore after the true time of the measurement.

xtce:Parameter.name: MAGDATA__BX
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: Magnetic field in MPU +X direction (AK +Y direction)

xtce:Parameter.name: MAGDATA__BY
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: Magnetic field in MPU +Y direction (AK +X direction)

xtce:Parameter.name: MAGDATA__BZ
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: Magnetic field in MPU +Z direction (AK -Z direction)

xtce:SequenceContainer.name: CCSDSPacket
xtce:SequenceContainer.xtce:LongDescription: Super-container for telemetry and command packets

xtce:SequenceContainer.name: SecondaryHeaderContainer
xtce:SequenceContainer.xtce:LongDescription: Container for telemetry secondary header items

xtce:SequenceContainer.name: MAG_DATA
xtce:SequenceContainer.xtce:LongDescription: Timestamp is from just after single-shot readout is commanded

xtce:SequenceContainer.name: BMP_DATA
xtce:SequenceContainer.xtce:LongDescription: Timestamp is after loop() notices that a complete temperature/pressure measurement is finished

xtce:SequenceContainer.name: NMEA
xtce:SequenceContainer.xtce:LongDescription: Timestamp is that of the time that loop() noticed it has a '$' to process, so the timestamp of the start of the *next* NMEA sentence

xtce:SequenceContainer.name: GGA
xtce:SequenceContainer.xtce:LongDescription: Timestamp is that of the time that loop() noticed that a GGA sentence has been parsed

xtce:SequenceContainer.name: RMC
xtce:SequenceContainer.xtce:LongDescription: Timestamp is that of the time that loop() noticed that an RMC sentence has been parsed

xtce:MetaCommand.name: CMD_PKT_HDR
xtce:MetaCommand.xtce:LongDescription: This is the CCSDS packet header for all commands

xtce:MetaCommand.name: CMD_SEC_HDR
xtce:MetaCommand.xtce:LongDescription: This is the command secondary header
